-- Air China Will Pay Up to $814 Million for 10 Airbus 320-Series Aircraft
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-30T15:24:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/air-china-will-pay-up-to-814-million-for-10-airbus-320-series-aircraft.html

          
          
             Air China Ltd. said one of its
airlines will buy 10 Airbus 320-series planes.  
 Shenzhen Airlines Ltd. signed a purchasing agreement with
Airbus SAS today, Air China said in a statement to the Shanghai
and Hong Kong stock exchanges. The company said the cost will be
less than what it described as a “basic price” of $814 million
for 10 planes.  
 The planes will be delivered in 2012 and 2013, according to
the statement.  
